After a three-week negotiating marathon, the trade unions of the street association and the TLF - the only employers' organisation that remained until the end - reached an agreement on Friday evening that puts an end to the strike order and the impending severe supply shortage at Christmas.
At the signing session on Friday evening, State Secretary for Transport Dominique Bussereau "welcomed" the agreement, which was initiated on Wednesday morning after several weeks of negotiations.
