New Silicon Valley
For many years it was considered a secret city, inaccessible to Western visitors.
Selenograd, one of ten districts of the capital Moscow, was in the Soviet Union a strictly guarded site for secret arms research.
Today, the municipality with its 216,000 inhabitants, 37 kilometers from Moscow's center, is considered "Russian Silicon Valley".
