Workshop cost estimate in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: identifying the vehicle, searching the spare part, creating and generating a cost estimate.
The ease of use of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an internet connection to use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified on the basis of the chassis number, a graph of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables, such as the price for the working hours, surcharges or discounts, and after that he can have the cost estimate printed out and passed on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for assessment like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can easily pay.
